CEVML ~ Churro's English Vocabulary Markup Language.

Keywords: 
> gUwUide [set/call]
    > gUwUide set [parameters]
        > “definition” to make definition cell visible.
        > “yes” to set all bits visibility.
        > “þesaurus/thesaurus” to simultaneously set antonyms/synonyms cells visibility.
        > “antonyms”, “synonyms” , “sentence” to set þeir resepctive cell visibility.
        > “antonyms” and “synonyms” can only be set if “þesaurus/thesaurus” is not set and vice versa.
        > “þesaurus/thesaurus” also always sets “antonyms” and “synonyms”.
        > Add a “-” to make þe cell invisible.
        > It can only be called once.
    > gUwUide call
        > No furþer parameters. Adds table guide as a row. 
> inwnfo [show/hide/custom]
    > inwnfo [show/hide]
        > No furþer parameters. Shows or hides þe identifying information.
    > inwnfo custom [string]
        Sets identifying information to custom text. Default is name, date, and period.
> dAwAte [string]
    > Sets date. Cannot be called if set inwnfo custom.
> OwOrds {[vocabulary]}
    > Sets vocabulary table.
    > Each entry is as follows: [Vocabulary word] :3 [Part of speech] ¦3 [Word definition] ^w^ [Synonyms] ⌄m⌄ [Antonyms] >w< [Sentence] ,w,
> &w&[string]
    >Calls a custom character. See function deSyntax in vocabulary.html
>

